  <Name>k__BackingField: Ecclesiastes
  fancyName: 
  nickname: ecc
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: PrologueMotto Introduced'
      title: PrologueMotto Introduced
      number: 1
      content: 'The words of the Teacher, the son of David, king in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: All Toil is Profitless and Repetitious'
      title: All Toil is Profitless and Repetitious
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CVanity of vanities!\u201D says the Teacher,  \u201CVanity of
        vanities! All is vanity!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'What does a person gain in all his toil with which he toils under
        the sun? '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'A generation goes, and a generation comes, but the earth stands forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The sun rises, and the sun goes down; to its place it hurries, and
        there it rises again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The wind goes to the south and goes around to the north; around and
        around it goes, and on its circuit the wind returns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All the streams flow to the sea, but the sea is never full; to the
        place where the streams flow, there they continue to flow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'All things toil continuously;  no one can ever finish describing
        this.  The eye is never satisfied with seeing, and the ear is never filled
        with hearing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "What has been\u2014it is what will be; what has been done\u2014it
        is what will be done; there is nothing new under the sun. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "There is a thing of which it is said, \u201CLook at this! This is
        new!\u201D But it already existed in ages past before us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Qohelet Introduces His Quest'
      title: Qohelet Introduces His Quest
      number: 11
      content: 'There is neither remembrance of former generations, nor will there
        be remembrance of future generations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I, the Teacher, was king over Israel in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I applied my mind to seek and to search by wisdom all that is done
        under the heavens. It is a grievous task God has given to humans.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I saw all the works that are done under the sun. Look! Everything
        is vanity and chasing wind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'What is twisted cannot be straightened,  and what is lacking cannot
        be counted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I said to myself, \u201CLook! I have become great and have increased
        in wisdom more than anyone who has preceded me over Jerusalem. I have acquired
        a great deal of wisdom and knowledge.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So I dedicated myself to learn about wisdom and to learn about delusion
        and folly. However, I discovered that this also is chasing wind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For in much wisdom is much frustration,  and whoever increases knowledge
        increases sorrow. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Qohelet\u2019s Investigation of Self-Indulgence"
      title: "Qohelet\u2019s Investigation of Self-Indulgence"
      number: 1
      content: "I said to myself, \u201CCome! I will test pleasure to see whether
        it is worthwhile.\u201D But look, \u201CThis also is vanity!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I said of laughter, \u201CIt is folly!\u201D and of pleasure, \u201CWhat
        does it accomplish?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: "3: Qohelet\u2019s Investigation of Personal Accomplishment"
      title: "Qohelet\u2019s Investigation of Personal Accomplishment"
      number: 3
      content: 'I also explored the effects of indulging my flesh with wine. My mind
        guiding me with wisdom, I investigated folly so that I might discover what
        is good under heaven for humans to do during the days of their lives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I accomplished great things. I built for myself houses; I planted
        for myself vineyards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I made for myself gardens and parks, and I planted all sorts of fruit
        trees in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I made for myself pools of water from which to irrigate a grove of
        flourishing trees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I acquired male slaves and female slaves, as well as children born
        in my house. I also had livestock, cattle, and flocks more than anyone who
        was before me in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I also gathered to myself silver and gold\u2014the royal and provincial
        treasuries. I acquired for myself male and female singers, as well as the
        delight of men, voluptuous concubines.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Thus, I accomplished far more than anyone who was before me in Jerusalem\u2014indeed,
        my wisdom stood by me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I neither withheld anything from my eyes that they desired, nor did
        I deprive any pleasure from my heart. My heart rejoiced in all my toil, for
        this was my reward from all my toil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Living Must Abandon the Work of their Hands to Others at Death'
      title: The Living Must Abandon the Work of their Hands to Others at Death
      number: 11
      content: "Yet when I considered all the effort which I expended and the toil
        with which I toiled to do, then behold, \u201CEverything is vanity and chasing
        wind! There is nothing profitable under the sun!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Next, I considered wisdom, as well as delusion and folly. What can
        anyone do who will come after the king that has not already been done? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I realized that wisdom has an advantage over folly, just as light
        has an advantage over darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The wise man can see where he is walking, but the fool walks in darkness.
        Yet I also realized that both of them suffer the same fate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So I said to myself, \u201CIf I also suffer the same fate as the
        fool, what advantage is my great wisdom?\u201D So I said to myself, \u201CThis
        also is vanity!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Certainly no one will remember the wise man or the fool in future
        generations. When future days come, both will have been forgotten already.
        How is it that the wise man dies the same as the fool? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So I hated life because the work done under the sun is grievous to
        me. For everything is vanity and chasing wind! '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So I hated all my toil with which I have toiled under the sun, for
        I must leave it behind to someone who will be after me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And who knows whether he will be wise or foolish? Yet he will exercise
        control of all the fruit of my toil with which I toiled wisely under the
        sun. This also is vanity! '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So I began to despair of all the toil with which I toiled under the
        sun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For although a person may toil with great wisdom and skill, he must
        leave his reward to someone who has not toiled for it. This also is vanity
        and a great calamity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For what does a person receive for all his toil and in the longing
        of his heart with which he toils under the sun? '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: It is Best to Simply Enjoy the Passing Pleasures of Life as Reward
        for Pleasing God'
      title: It is Best to Simply Enjoy the Passing Pleasures of Life as Reward for
        Pleasing God
      number: 23
      content: 'All his days are painful, his labor brings grief, and his heart cannot
        rest at night. This also is vanity! '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'There is nothing better for a person than to eat and drink and find
        delight in his toil. For I also realized that this is from the hand of God! '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For who can eat and drink, and who can enjoy life apart from him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For to the person who is good in his eyes, he gives wisdom, knowledge,
        and joy; but to the sinner he gives the task of gathering and heaping up
        only to give it to him who is pleasing to him. This also is vanity and chasing
        wind! '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Has Ordained the Ebb and Flow of Human Activities'
      title: God Has Ordained the Ebb and Flow of Human Activities
      number: 1
      content: 'For everything there is an appointed time, a time for every matter
        under heaven: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'a time to bear and a time to die; a time to plant and a time to root
        up what is planted; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'a time to kill and a time to heal; a time to break down and a time
        to build up; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'a time to weep and a time to laugh; a time to mourn and a time to
        dance; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'a time to throw away stones and a time to gather stones; a time to
        embrace and a time to refrain from embracing; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'a time to seek and a time to lose; a time to keep and a time to throw
        away; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'a time to tear and a time to sew; a time to be silent and a time
        to speak; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'a time to love and a time to hate; a time for war and a time for
        peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: No One Understands God\u2019s Mysterious Plan"
      title: "No One Understands God\u2019s Mysterious Plan"
      number: 9
      content: 'What does the worker gain in his toil? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I have seen the busyness God gives to humans to preoccupy them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He has made everything suitable in its time. He also has put the
        past in their hearts, yet no one can grasp what God does from the beginning
        to the end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So I realized that there is nothing better for them than to rejoice
        and enjoy themselves during their lives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And for anyone to eat and drink, that is, to enjoy the fruit of all
        his toil, this also is a gift of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I know everything God does endures forever; nothing can be added
        to it, and nothing can be taken from it, for God so acts that humans might
        stand in awe before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: "15: God\u2019s Mysterious Plan Allows Injustice to Exist in the World"
      title: "God\u2019s Mysterious Plan Allows Injustice to Exist in the World"
      number: 15
      content: "What is\u2014it already was, and what will be\u2014it already is,
        for God will do what he has done.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I saw something else under the sun: instead of justice there was
        evil; instead of righteousness there was wickedness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So I said to myself, \u201CGod will surely judge the righteous and
        the wicked, for he has appointed a time of judgment for every deed and every
        work.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I said to myself concerning humans, \u201CGod sifts them in order
        to show them that they are like beasts.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For the fate of humans and the fate of the beast is the same. The
        death of the one is like the death of the other, for both are mortal. Man
        has no advantage over the beast, for both are fleeting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Both go to one place\u2014both came from dust and both return to
        dust. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For no one knows whether the spirit of a human ascends to heaven
        and whether the spirit of the beast descends to the ground! '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So I concluded that there is nothing better for a person than to
        enjoy the fruit of his labor, for this is his lot in life. For no one knows
        what will happen in the future.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Existence of Oppression in the World Makes Human Existence Miserable'
      title: The Existence of Oppression in the World Makes Human Existence Miserable
      number: 1
      content: "I looked again, and I saw all the oppression that occurs under the
        sun. I saw the tears of the oppressed\u2014 no one comforts them! Those who
        oppress them are powerful\u2014 no one can comfort them!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I deemed the dead who have already died more fortunate than the
        living who are still alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: People Need Balance in Their Approach to Labor'
      title: People Need Balance in Their Approach to Labor
      number: 3
      content: 'But better off than both of them is the one who has not yet been
        born and has not seen the evil deeds that are done under the sun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I also realized that all of the toil and all of the skillful work
        that is done\u2014it is envy between one man and another. This also is vanity
        and chasing wind! "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The fool refuses to work with his hands, so he has nothing to eat
        except his own skin!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Wealth without Someone with Which to Enjoy It is Futile'
      title: Wealth without Someone with Which to Enjoy It is Futile
      number: 6
      content: 'Better is one handful with peace than two fists full with toil and
        chasing wind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I turned again and saw another vanity under the sun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Friends and Family Can Help One Another in Life'
      title: Friends and Family Can Help One Another in Life
      number: 8
      content: "Sometimes a man is all alone with no companion; he also has neither
        son nor brother. Yet there is no end to all his toil, and his eye is not
        satisfied with wealth. He laments, \u201CFor whom am I toiling and depriving
        myself of pleasure?\u201D This also is vanity\u2014it is an unhappy business! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Two are better than the one, for they enjoy a better reward for their
        toil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For if one falls, his companion may help him up. But pity the one
        who falls and there is no one to help him up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Also if two lie together, they can keep each other warm. But how
        can one person be warm? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: One Must Be Willing to Listen to Counsel'
      title: One Must Be Willing to Listen to Counsel
      number: 12
      content: 'Although an assailant may overpower one person, two may withstand
        him. A threefold cord is not easily broken!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'A poor but wise youth is better than an old but foolish king who
        no longer knows how to receive advice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For he came out of the prison house to reign, since he was born poor
        in his kingdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I saw all the living who move about under the sun with the youth;
        the second who will stand in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'There is no end to all the people, to all who were before him. Yet
        the later generation will not rejoice in him, for this also is vanity and
        chasing wind! '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Listen to God Rather Than Uttering Rash Vows'
      title: Listen to God Rather Than Uttering Rash Vows
      number: 1
      content: ' Guard your steps when you go to the house of God; draw near to listen
        rather than to offer a sacrifice of fools, for they do not know that they
        are doing evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Do not be rash with your mouth, and do not let your heart be quick
        to utter a word before God. For God is in heaven, and you are on earth; therefore,
        let your words be few. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For a dream comes with many cares, and the voice of a fool with many
        words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When you make a vow to God, do not delay in fulfilling it, for he
        takes no pleasure in fools. Fulfill what you vow! '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'It is better that you not vow than that you vow and not fulfill it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Do not let your mouth lead your flesh into sin, and do not tell the
        messenger that it was a mistake. Why anger God at your words, so that he
        destroys the work of your hands? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Powerful Bureaucrats Exploit the Helpless Poor'
      title: Powerful Bureaucrats Exploit the Helpless Poor
      number: 7
      content: 'For with many dreams come vanities and numerous words. Therefore,
        fear God! '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Do not be surprised if you see the poor being oppressed with violence
        or do not see justice and righteousness in the province. For one official
        is watched by a higher official, and there are even higher officials over
        them! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: There is Never Enough Money to Satisfy'
      title: There is Never Enough Money to Satisfy
      number: 9
      content: 'The produce of the land is exploited by everyone; even the king profits
        from the field of the poor!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Whoever loves money is not satisfied with money, and whoever loves
        wealth is not satisfied with profit. This also is vanity! '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When prosperity increases, those who consume it increase. So its
        owner gains nothing, except to see his wealth before it is spent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Hoarding Wealth Can Backfire'
      title: Hoarding Wealth Can Backfire
      number: 12
      content: 'The sleep of the laborer is pleasant, whether he eats little or much,
        but the wealth of the rich man does not allow him to rest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'There is a grievous evil which I have seen under the sun: wealth
        hoarded by its owner to his harm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'That wealth was lost in a bad venture. Although he has borne a child,
        he has nothing to leave to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Just as he came from his mother\u2019s womb naked, he will depart
        just as he came; he will take nothing with him for his toil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'This also is a grievous illness. Exactly as he came, so he will go.
        What profit does he gain for all his toil for the wind? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: If You Have Wealth, Enjoy It as God Enables'
      title: If You Have Wealth, Enjoy It as God Enables
      number: 17
      content: 'Also, he eats in darkness all his days; he is frustrated in much
        sickness and resentment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Look! I have discovered what is good and fitting: to eat and to drink
        and to enjoy all the fruit of the toil with which one toils under the sun
        during the number of the days of his life that God gives to him\u2014for
        this is his lot.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'This indeed is a gift of God: everyone to whom God gives wealth and
        possessions, he also empowers him to enjoy them, to accept his lot, and to
        rejoice in the fruit of his toil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For he does not remember the brief days of his life, for God keeps
        his heart preoccupied with enjoyment of life. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Those Who Have Wealth but Do Not Enjoy It Are Pitiful'
      title: Those Who Have Wealth but Do Not Enjoy It Are Pitiful
      number: 1
      content: 'Here is another misfortune that I have seen under the sun, and it
        is prevalent among humankind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "God gives a man wealth, possessions, and honor, so that he lacks
        nothing his heart desires; yet God does not enable him to enjoy it\u2014instead
        someone else ends up enjoying it. This is vanity\u2014indeed, it is a grievous
        ill! "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Even if a man fathers a hundred children and lives many years so
        that the days of his years are many, if his heart is not satisfied with his
        prosperity and he does not receive a proper burial, I deem the stillborn
        better than him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For he comes into vanity and departs into darkness, and his name
        is shrouded in darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He has neither seen nor known the sun, yet he has more rest than
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: One Must Learn to Be Content with What One Has'
      title: One Must Learn to Be Content with What One Has
      number: 6
      content: 'Even if a man lives a thousand years twice, if he does not enjoy
        prosperity, both suffer the same fate!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "All of a man\u2019s toil is for his mouth\u2014 yet his appetite
        is never satisfied. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So do the wise really have an advantage over fools? Can the poor
        really gain anything by knowing how to act in front of others?  '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: It is Futile for Humans to Complain about God\u2019s Irresistible
        Will"
      title: "It is Futile for Humans to Complain about God\u2019s Irresistible Will"
      number: 9
      content: 'Better to be content with what your eyes see than for your soul to
        constantly crave more.  This also is vanity and chasing wind! '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Whatever is\u2014it was already determined, what will be\u2014it
        has already been decided.  As for man, he cannot argue against what is more
        powerful than him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Future is Inscrutable to Humans'
      title: The Future is Inscrutable to Humans
      number: 11
      content: 'Increasing words only multiplies futility,  how does that profit
        anyone? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For who knows what is good for a man in his life during the few days
        of his fleeting life, which are fleeting as a shadow? For who can tell anyone
        what will happen in the future under the sun? '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: People Generally Do Not Know What is Best for Them'
      title: People Generally Do Not Know What is Best for Them
      number: 1
      content: "A good name is better than precious ointment, and the day of death
        is better than the day of one\u2019s birth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Better to go to the house of mourning than to go to the house of
        feasting, for death is the end of every person, and the living should take
        it to his heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Sorrow is better than laughter, for by sadness of countenance the
        heart is made good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The heart of the wise is in the house of mourning, but the heart
        of fools is in the house of mirth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Better to listen to the rebuke of the wise than for a man to listen
        to the song of fools. '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Wisdom\u2014Although Vulnerable\u2014is Beneficial"
      title: "Wisdom\u2014Although Vulnerable\u2014is Beneficial"
      number: 6
      content: 'Like the sound of thorns under a pot, so also the laughter of fools.
        This also is vanity! '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Surely oppression makes a fool of the wise, and a bribe corrupts
        the heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The end of a matter is better than its beginning; better to be slow
        to anger than hot-headed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not be quick in your spirit to anger, for anger lodges in the
        bosom of fools. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Do not say, \u201CWhy were the former days better than these?\u201D
        For it is not from wisdom that you ask this. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Wisdom is good with an inheritance; it benefits the living.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: Humans Must Accept God\u2019s Will and Make the Best of It"
      title: "Humans Must Accept God\u2019s Will and Make the Best of It"
      number: 12
      content: "For wisdom offers protection like money offers protection.  But knowledge
        has an advantage\u2014wisdom restores life to its possessor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Consider the work of God. For who is able to make straight what he
        made crooked? '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: The Law of Retribution Does Not Always Work\u2014but It Does Sometimes"
      title: "The Law of Retribution Does Not Always Work\u2014but It Does Sometimes"
      number: 14
      content: 'In the day of prosperity, rejoice! But in the day of adversity, consider!
        For God made one in place of another so that mortals cannot find out what
        will happen in the future.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I have seen all these things in my vain life: Sometimes a righteous
        man perishes in spite of his righteousness, and sometimes a wicked man lives
        a long life in spite of his evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Do not be excessively righteous, and do not act excessively wise,
        lest you destroy yourself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do not act excessively wicked, and do not be a fool, lest you die
        before your time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Wisdom is Valuable, but No One is Completely Righteous'
      title: Wisdom is Valuable, but No One is Completely Righteous
      number: 18
      content: 'It is good to take hold of the one and also must not let go of the
        other; for whoever fears God will hold both of them secure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Wisdom gives more strength to the wise than ten rulers who are in
        the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Surely there is no one righteous on the earth who continually does
        good and never sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Do not pay attention to everything people say, lest you hear your
        own servant curse you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Absolute Wisdom is Unattainable'
      title: Absolute Wisdom is Unattainable
      number: 22
      content: 'For your heart knows that you also have cursed others many times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "All this I have tested with wisdom. I said, \u201CI will be wise!\u201D
        but it was beyond my grasp.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Whatever is\u2014it is far beyond comprehension. Who can discover
        it? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I set my mind to try to seek wisdom and the plan, and to know that
        wickedness is foolishness and that folly is delusion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I myself found that more bitter than death is the woman who is a
        trap, whose heart is a snare, and whose hands are bonds. The one who pleases
        God escapes from her, but the sinner is caught by her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CLook! I found this,\u201D said the Teacher, \u201Cwhile trying
        to find how the plan fits together. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'What my heart sought, I did not find. Although I found one righteous
        man among one thousand, I did not find one upright woman among all these. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Look! This alone I found: God made mankind upright, but they have
        devised many schemes.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wisdom is Valuable'
      title: Wisdom is Valuable
      number: 1
      content: "Who is like the sage? Who knows the interpretation of a thing? A
        man\u2019s wisdom makes his face shine, and the hardness of his face is changed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Keep the command of the king  because of your oath to God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do not be terrified of his presence! Go at once and do not delay
        when a matter is unpleasant, for he can do anything that he desires. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Since the word of the king is supreme, no one can say to him, \u201CWhat
        are you doing?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Whoever obeys his command will not suffer disaster. The wise mind
        knows the proper time and the right procedure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: No One Knows the Future'
      title: No One Knows the Future
      number: 6
      content: 'For there is a proper time and right procedure for every matter,
        even though the trouble of man weighs heavy upon him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Surely no one knows what will be, so who can tell anyone what will
        happen? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The World Marred by Oppression and Injustice'
      title: The World Marred by Oppression and Injustice
      number: 8
      content: 'Just as no one can control the wind to restrain the wind, so also
        no one can control the day of his death. Just as no one is discharged in
        time of war, so wickedness will not deliver the wicked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I saw all this as I applied my heart to all the deeds done under
        the sun: sometimes those in authority harm others.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Although Evil is Not Punished Swiftly, God Does Eventually Punish
        Sinners'
      title: Although Evil is Not Punished Swiftly, God Does Eventually Punish Sinners
      number: 10
      content: 'Meanwhile, I saw the wicked being honorably buried, but those who
        came and went from the holy place were forgotten in the city, even though
        they had done so. This also is vanity! '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Because sentence against an evil deed is not carried out quickly,
        the heart of humans fills up within them to do evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Although the sinner does evil a hundred times and prolongs his life,
        yet I also know that it will be good for those who fear God\u2014because
        they fear his presence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But it will not go well with the wicked, and they will not prolong
        their days, like the shadow; because there is no fearing God\u2019s presence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Humans Should Enjoy the Life That God Gives to Them'
      title: Humans Should Enjoy the Life That God Gives to Them
      number: 14
      content: "There is a vanity that happens on earth: sometimes the righteous
        suffer what the wicked deserve, and sometimes the wicked receive what the
        righteous deserve. I said, \u201CThis also is vanity!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: No One Can Discover the Rhyme and Reason for Things'
      title: No One Can Discover the Rhyme and Reason for Things
      number: 15
      content: 'So I recommend enjoyment. For there is nothing better for man under
        the sun than to eat and to drink and to rejoice. This will accompany him
        in his toil the days of his life that God gives to him under the sun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I applied my mind to know wisdom and to understand the business that
        is done on earth\u2014how neither day nor night one\u2019s eyes see sleep. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then I saw all the work of God\u2014man is not able to discover the
        work that is done under the sun. Although man may toil in seeking, he cannot
        find it. Even if a wise man claims that he knows it, he cannot find it. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Same Fate\u2014Death\u2014Awaits Everyone"
      title: "The Same Fate\u2014Death\u2014Awaits Everyone"
      number: 1
      content: 'So all this I laid to my heart, and I concluded that the righteous
        and the wise, as well as their deeds, are in the hand of God. So no one knows
        anything that will come to them, whether it will be love or hatred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The same fate comes to everyone: to the righteous and to the wicked,
        to the good and to the wicked,  to the clean and to the unclean, to those
        who sacrifice and to those who do not sacrifice. As with the good man, so
        also to the sinner; as with those who swear an oath, so also those who fear
        oaths. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Death Deprives Humans of Everything in Life'
      title: Death Deprives Humans of Everything in Life
      number: 3
      content: 'This is the injustice that is done under the sun: the same fate comes
        to everyone. Also the hearts of humans are full of evil; delusion is in their
        hearts during their lives, and then they die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Whoever is joined to all the living has hope. After all, even a live
        dog is better than a dead lion! '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For the living know that they will die, but the dead do not know
        anything. They no longer have a reward, and even the memory of them is forgotten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Enjoy Life While It Lasts'
      title: Enjoy Life While It Lasts
      number: 6
      content: 'What they loved and hated, as well as what they desired, has already
        perished. They no longer have any share in what is done under the sun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Go\u2014eat your food with joy, and drink your wine with a merry
        heart! For God already has approved your deeds. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Always be clothed in white garments, and never let your head lack
        oil! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Enjoy life with the wife whom you love all the days of your vain
        life which he gives you under the sun, because this is your lot in life and
        in the toil with which you toil under the sun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Injustice of Time and Chance'
      title: The Injustice of Time and Chance
      number: 10
      content: "Whatever your hand finds to do\u2014do it with all your might; for
        in Sheol\u2014where you are going\u2014no one works, plans, knows, or thinks
        about anything. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I looked again and saw under the sun that the race does not belong
        to the swift, the battle does not belong to the mighty, food does not belong
        to the wise, wealth does not belong to the intelligent, and success does
        not belong to the skillful, for time and chance befalls all of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: Wisdom\u2014Although Vulnerable\u2014is Superior to Power"
      title: "Wisdom\u2014Although Vulnerable\u2014is Superior to Power"
      number: 12
      content: 'For man does not know his time. Just as fish are caught in a cruel
        net and like birds who are seized in a snare, so also humans are ensnared
        at a cruel time when it falls suddenly upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I have also seen this example of wisdom under the sun, and it seemed
        great to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'There was a small city with few people in it. A great king came and
        besieged it, building great siege works against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now, a poor wise man was found in it, and he delivered the city by
        his wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: "16: Wisdom\u2014Although Vulnerable\u2014is Superior to Folly"
      title: "Wisdom\u2014Although Vulnerable\u2014is Superior to Folly"
      number: 16
      content: 'So I concluded that wisdom is better than might, yet the wisdom of
        the poor is despised, and his words are not heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The words of the wise are heard in peace more than the shouting of
        a ruler is heard among the fools. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Wisdom is better than weapons of war, but one sinner destroys much
        good. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: ' Dead flies cause a bad smell and ruin the ointment of the perfumer.
        So also a little folly outweighs wisdom and honor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The heart of the wise inclines to his right, but the heart of the
        fool inclines to his left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Even when the fool walks along the road, he lacks sense; he tells
        everyone that he is a fool. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If the anger of the ruler rises against you, do not leave your post,
        for calmness can undo great offenses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "There is an evil I have seen under the sun\u2014 it is an error that
        proceeds from a ruler! "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The fool is set in many high places, but the rich sit in lowly places. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Accidents Happen\u2014Even to Professionals"
      title: "Accidents Happen\u2014Even to Professionals"
      number: 7
      content: 'I have even seen slaves riding on horses and princes walking like
        slaves on the earth! '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Whoever digs a pit will fall into it. Whoever breaks through a wall,
        a snake will bite him. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Hard Work and Skill Alone Cannot Succeed\u2014Wisdom is Necessary"
      title: "Hard Work and Skill Alone Cannot Succeed\u2014Wisdom is Necessary"
      number: 9
      content: 'Whoever quarries stones will be wounded by them. Whoever splits logs
        will be endangered by them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If the ax is blunt but one does not sharpen its edge, he must exert
        more effort,  but the advantage of wisdom is it brings success. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Consequences of Foolishness'
      title: The Consequences of Foolishness
      number: 11
      content: 'If the snake bites before the charming, the snake charmer will not
        succeed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The wise man wins favor by the words of his mouth, but the fool is
        devoured by his own lips. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He begins by saying what is foolish and ends by uttering what is
        wicked delusion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The fool talks too much,  for no one knows what will be. Who can
        tell anyone what will happen in the future?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The fool is so worn out by a hard day\u2019s work he cannot even
        find his way home at night.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Woe to you, O land, when your king is a youth and your princes feast
        in the morning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Blessed are you, O land, when your king is a son of nobility and
        your princes feast at the proper time\u2014 to gain strength and not to get
        drunk. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Through sloth the roof sinks in, and through idleness of hands the
        house leaks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Feasts are held for celebration,  wine cheers the living, and money
        answers everything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do not curse the king even in your thoughts, and do not curse the
        rich even in your own bedroom, for a bird of the sky may carry your voice;
        a winged messenger may repeat your words. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Living in the Light of the Limits of Human Knowledge'
      title: Living in the Light of the Limits of Human Knowledge
      number: 1
      content: 'Send out your bread on the water, for in many days you will find
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Divide your share in seven or in eight, for you do not know what
        disaster will happen on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "When the clouds are full, they empty rain on the earth. Whether a
        tree falls to the south or whether it falls to the north, the place where
        the tree falls\u2014there it will be. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Whoever watches the wind will not sow; whoever watches the clouds
        will not reap. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Just as you do not know how the path of the wind goes, nor how the
        bones of a fetus form in a mother\u2019s womb, so you do not know the work
        of God who makes everything. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Enjoy Life to the Fullest within the Auspices of the Fear of God'
      title: Enjoy Life to the Fullest within the Auspices of the Fear of God
      number: 6
      content: "Sow your seed in the morning, and do not let your hands rest in the
        evening, for you do not know what will prosper\u2014 whether this or that,
        or whether both of them alike will succeed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The light is sweet, and it is pleasant for the eyes to see the sun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For if a man lives many years, let him rejoice in all of them! Let
        him remember that the days of the darkness will be many\u2014 all that is
        coming is vanity! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Rejoice, O young man, in your youth, and let your heart cheer you
        in the days of your youth! Follow the ways of your heart and the sight of
        your eyes\u2014 but know that God will bring you into judgment for all these
        things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Banish anxiety from your heart, and put away pain from your body,
        for youth and vigor are vanity. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Advice to the Young: Life is Short and Then You Die'
      title: 'Advice to the Young: Life is Short and Then You Die'
      number: 1
      content: "Remember your Creator in the days of your youth\u2014 before the
        days of trouble come and the years draw near when you will say, \u201CI find
        no pleasure in them!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Before the sun, the light, the moon, and the stars darken and the
        clouds return after the rain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When the guards of the house tremble, and the men of strength are
        bent; the grinders cease because they are few, and those looking through
        the windows see dimly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When the doors on the street are shut, when the sound of the grinding
        mill is low; one rises up to the sound of the bird, and all the daughters
        of song are brought low. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They are afraid of heights, and terrors are on the road. The almond
        tree blossoms, and the grasshopper draws itself along, and desire fails because
        man goes to his eternal home, and the mourners go about in the streets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Before the silver cord is snapped and the golden bowl is broken;
        and the jar at the foundation is broken, and the wheel at the cistern is
        broken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Motto Restated'
      title: Motto Restated
      number: 7
      content: 'And the dust returns to the earth as it was, and the breath returns
        to God who gave it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Epilogue'
      title: Epilogue
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CVanity of vanity!\u201D says the Teacher.  \u201CEverything
        is vanity!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Teacher was full of wisdom, and he taught the people with knowledge.
        He carefully considered many proverbs and carefully arranged them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The Teacher sought to find delightful words, and he wrote what is
        upright\u2014truthful words. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The words of the wise are like cattle goads; the collections of the
        sages are like pricks inflicted by one shepherd.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'My son, be careful about anything beyond these things. For the writing
        of books is endless, and too much study is wearisome.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
